  body
    .reveal
      .slides

        section#title
          h1 Applying to (CS) Graduate School
          h3 A 30,000-Foot View
          p
            a(href='http://scottcheng.com/', target='_blank') 程烨 / Scott Cheng
          p
            a(href='http://eecs.pku.edu.cn/', target='_blank') PKU CS
            |  ➞ 
            a(href='http://cs.stanford.edu/', target='_blank') Stanford MSCS

        section#crossroad
          p Welcome to the crossroad of your life.
            //- Graduate application is all about making choices.
            //- When your decision is made, everything else comes naturally.
          p
            | Ask yourself: 
            i which way would you go?

        section#know-what-you-want
          h2 What Do You Want?
            //- This "theme" goes through the entire application process.
            //- You don't have to figure out everything at the beginning,
            //- but somewhere down the journey, you'll have to be very clear.
          ul
            li Why study abroad?
              //- Why study in the US
            li Why study in a particular field?
              //- Why computer science
            li Why school? Why program?
              //- Why Stanford? Why MSCS?
            li How does the program fit into the bigger picture of your life?
          p If you don't have a clue, think twice about applying.

        //- section#ms-vs-phd
          h2 MS or PhD
          ul
            li
              | Do you 
              i love
              |  doing research?
            li Do you want a career as a researcher?

        section#program-selection
          h2 Choosing Your Program
          ul
            li What the program has to offer
              //- Tracks, courses, capstone projects, thesis
              //- Pure CS or multidisciplinary
            li Prestige of program
              //- Ranking, reputation
            li Location
              //- Weather, downtown or uptown
            li Culture
              //- Startup culture in Stanford and SF Bay Area
            li External resources
              //- d.school, GSB, silicon valley
              //- Beyond the program

        section#program-researching
          h2 Research the Programs
          ul
            li Read (peruse) the program website
            li Talk to students and professors there
          blockquote Know the program, and know your reasons for choosing it.

        section#my-criteria
          h2 My Program-Hunting Criteria
          ul
            li Master's program
            li Focused on CS and HCI
            li Strong CS dept, strong HCI lab
            li Location &amp; culture
              //- Hacker culture: Bay Area, Boston, Austin, Seattle, ...

        section#where-i-applied
          h2 Where I applied
          ul
            li Stanford MSCS, UCSD MSCS, UMD MSCS, GaTech MSCS, UCI MSICS
              //- Mater in CS with HCI specialization
            li CMU MHCI, GaTech MSHCI
              //- HCI program under CS school
            li UCLA MSCS, UT Austin MSCS, USC MSCS, NYU MSCS, CMU MSIT-VLIS
              //- Other CS programs, for location, prestige, etc

        section#where-i-did-not-apply
          h2 Where I did NOT apply
          ul
            li MIT MSCS, UCB MSCS
              //- Research-oriented
            li UWash HCDE, NYU ITP
              //- Pure HCI programs

        section#package
          h2 Application Packet
            //- After setting your targets, go to their websites and find out what they require from you.
          p
            | Convince the admission committee that you are 
            b qualified
            |  and 
            b motivated
            |  to succeed in your proposed program.
            //- What student does the program look for? convince them that you are that student.
          ul
            li Transcript
            li Standardized Tests (GRE, TOEFL)
            li: i Letter of Recommendation
            li: i Statement of Purpose
            li Resume / CV

        section#sop
          h2 Statement of Purpose
          blockquote
            p The Statement of Purpose required by grad schools is probably the hardest thing you will ever write.
            .author: a(href='http://www.uni.edu/~gotera/gradapp/stmtpurpose.htm', target='_blank') Vince Gotera

        section#sop-how
          h2 How to write your SoP?
          ul
            li Before you start, read what others say about it.
            li When you are happy with your draft, ask people to read it.
              ul
                li (Successful) former applicants
                li (Trusted) professionals who help people apply
            li Collect the feedback. Revise. Rewrite.

        section#resources
          h2 Resources
          ul
            li EndlessOffering Google Group &amp; Google Drive
            li: a(href='http://www.1point3acres.com/bbs/') 一亩三分地 (good starting point)
            li(style='font-size:.9em'): a(href='http://nlp.stanford.edu/~rkarthik/DAGAP.pdf', target='_blank') Demystifying the American Graduate Admissions Process
            li Google

        section#end
          h1 Thank You
          h2 Questions?

